!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

mixture /ˈmɪkstʃə/

(mixtures) 

1. N-SING A mixture of things consists of several different things together. 混合 

例： They looked at him with a mixture of horror, envy, and awe. 他们带着害怕、羡慕和敬畏的混合表情看着他。 

2. N-COUNT A mixture is a substance that consists of other substances which have been stirred or shaken together. 混合物 

例： ...a mixture of water and sugar and salt. …水、糖和盐的混合物。

</div>

